com.nimsoft.nimbus.ci
Class RemoteDevice

java.lang.Object
  com.nimsoft.nimbus.ci.Device
      com.nimsoft.nimbus.ci.RemoteDevice

public class RemoteDevice
extends Device

Represents a remote device that is being monitored.

A remote device is uniquely identified by the IP address of the device being monitored and the local Robot's device ID .

getMD5

public String getMD5()
              throws NimException,
                     UnknownHostException
Return the probe specific MD5 digest for this device. The MD5 digest includes the probe that found the device and the IP address of the device being monitored. Also, the name lookup (if needed) is deferred until this point (so this might be time-consuming.) This digest is intended to be used for setting the dev_id of the device

Specified by:
getMD5 in class Device
Returns:
An MD5 digest of the robot ID concatenated with the probe name and remote device's IP address.
Throws:
UnknownHostException - if name resolution fails.
NimException - unlikely

getProbeIndependentMD5

protected String getProbeIndependentMD5()
                                 throws NimException,
                                        UnknownHostException
Return the MD5 digest for this device. The MD5 digest includes the device and the IP address of the device being monitored. This digest is intended for use by the CI and MI key generation process (i.e., this is left around for backwards compat.)

Returns:
An MD5 digest of the robot ID concatenated with both the probe name and the remote device's IP address.
Throws:
UnknownHostException - if name resolution fails.
NimException - unlikely
